We still gotta deal with that tree.

246
00:11:05,623 --> 00:11:08,250
[chuckles] I'm not touching that tree
until you pay your rent.

247
00:11:08,334 --> 00:11:11,045
-Which just went up because of that.
-What?

248
00:11:11,128 --> 00:11:13,506
And stay the hell away from
my Dippin' Dots!

249
00:11:13,589 --> 00:11:16,967
You will never taste
the ice cream of the future.

250
00:11:24,183 --> 00:11:26,435
-Pistach--
-I am not in the mood!

251
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:29,730
[rock music playing]

252
00:11:30,314 --> 00:11:31,565
Hi, Jay.

253
00:11:32,274 --> 00:11:33,526
Mrs. Forman?

254
00:11:33,609 --> 00:11:35,361
It's time we had a little chat.

255
00:11:36,487 --> 00:11:37,613
How did you know I was here?

256
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:41,367
Oh, this is my town, sweetie.
I have eyes everywhere.

257
00:11:43,327 --> 00:11:44,495
How's Leia doing?

258
00:11:44,995 --> 00:11:49,041
I mean, I feel really bad about
how things went down, but I had to do it.

259
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:51,836
Well, that is what
I wanted to talk to you about.

260
00:11:51,919 --> 00:11:55,172
She is so upset,
she may not come back next summer.

261
00:11:55,256 --> 00:11:56,382
That's not what I wanted.

262
00:11:56,465 --> 00:11:58,092
This isn't about you!

263
00:11:59,927 --> 00:12:02,555
[forced laughter]

264
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:07,101
No, no, it <i>is</i> about you, honey.
You were saying?

265
00:12:07,184 --> 00:12:09,395
I wasn't trying to hurt her, Mrs. Forman.

266
00:12:09,895 --> 00:12:13,983
It's just, you know, anything can happen.
What if she meets someone else?

267
00:12:14,066 --> 00:12:17,153
Or what if I get asked
to star in the next <i>Karate Kid?</i>

268
00:12:17,236 --> 00:12:19,238
I mean, I'd have to move to Reseda!

269
00:12:22,116 --> 00:12:23,117
Okay, okay.

270
00:12:24,493 --> 00:12:28,330
Let me tell you a little story about
a long distance relationship of mine.

271
00:12:29,081 --> 00:12:32,293
I was dating this boy
I was madly in love with.

272
00:12:32,376 --> 00:12:35,671
And then the war started.
He was being shipped overseas.

273
00:12:35,755 --> 00:12:36,922
World War I?

274
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:44,764
[sharp exhale]

275
00:12:44,847 --> 00:12:48,642
Anyway, we decided
we would still give it a shot.

276
00:12:49,143 --> 00:12:51,687
And I never regretted that decision.

277
00:12:51,771 --> 00:12:52,813
And that guy was Red?

278
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:54,982
No, I think his name was Steve.

279
00:12:55,065 --> 00:12:57,318
So your point is
long distance doesn't work?

280
00:12:57,401 --> 00:12:58,402
Not with Steve.

281
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:01,572
He had a giant belly button.

282
00:13:02,364 --> 00:13:04,033
I could see it through his sweaters.

283
00:13:07,161 --> 00:13:10,414
The point is, at least we tried.

284
00:13:10,998 --> 00:13:14,502
Honey, don't go through life
wondering what could have been.

285
00:13:15,211 --> 00:13:17,797
You're squeezing my hand pretty hard,
Mrs. Forman. [chuckles]

286
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:20,549
I <i>really</i> want you to give it a try.

287
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:22,218
It's getting tighter.

288
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:24,553
I open a lot of mayonnaise jars.

289
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:27,264
[rock guitar riff playing]

290
00:13:27,932 --> 00:13:29,225
Shh.

291
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:32,228
A fly landed on my crotch, and I'm trying
to decide if it's worth the swat.

292
00:13:33,854 --> 00:13:36,315
-[fly buzzing]
-Damn. It flew away.

293
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:38,609
That's probably a good thing.

294
00:13:39,109 --> 00:13:41,862
-Oh, where's Gwen?
-She's out somewhere.

295
00:13:42,446 --> 00:13:44,698
I don't want to leave
without saying goodbye to her.

296
00:13:44,782 --> 00:13:46,408
I totally overreacted.

297
00:13:47,034 --> 00:13:50,538
This is my first breakup,
and I'm not handling it too well.

298
00:13:51,121 --> 00:13:52,581
Yeah, it sucks.

299
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:56,210
My first breakup felt like my heart
was getting ripped out of my butt, so…

300
00:13:56,293 --> 00:13:59,797
And it made it even worse
that everyone was agreeing with Jay.

301
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:01,757
Not everyone.

302
00:14:02,716 --> 00:14:05,469
Look, I was in a tough spot
'cause Jay's my best friend, but

303
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:07,680
I agree with you.

304
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:09,390
-You do?
-Yeah.

305
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:12,476
And then Nikki chimed in
talking about living separate lives,

306
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:15,938
and… I got worried I'd get
my heart ripped out of my butt again.

307
00:14:16,939 --> 00:14:18,524
Come on, Nate. That's just how she is.

308
00:14:19,108 --> 00:14:21,944
I know. I just…
I wish she wasn't always so…

309
00:14:22,653 --> 00:14:25,531
-God, there just isn't a word for it.
-Practical?

310
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:28,367
Cool. We just invented a word!

311
00:14:30,119 --> 00:14:32,162
Well, thanks for telling me
all this, Nate.

312
00:14:32,246 --> 00:14:34,707
It's nice to know there's
another hopeless romantic out there.

313
00:14:34,790 --> 00:14:37,835
[chuckles] Yeah.
I mean, what's more powerful than love?

314
00:14:38,586 --> 00:14:40,170
Maybe lightning. But that's it.

315
00:14:40,254 --> 00:14:44,550
Right. If two people are meant to be,
then they can survive anything.

316
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:45,467
Exactly.

317
00:14:46,093 --> 00:14:49,305
Do you know how lucky it is
to find that special person?

318
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:51,056
Someone who you feel comfortable with?

319
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:53,809
-And someone you can talk to.
-And everything's just easy.

320
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:56,103
-Right. I mean, someone who just…
-Gets you?

321
00:14:57,187 --> 00:14:58,898
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

322
00:15:01,525 --> 00:15:02,735
What the hell?!

323
00:15:04,987 --> 00:15:06,238
-Leia?!
-Gwen?!

324
00:15:06,322 --> 00:15:07,573
-Nate?!
-Gwen?!

325
00:15:13,245 --> 00:15:14,580
There was a fly on my junk.

326
00:15:14,663 --> 00:15:18,959
[rock music playing]

327
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:21,503
[chill rock music playing]

328
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:23,756
Oh, that Fenton makes my blood boil.

329
00:15:24,924 --> 00:15:27,051
But I also want to be there for Sherri.

330
00:15:27,718 --> 00:15:29,803
Oh, so much drama. Right, mama?

331
00:15:31,847 --> 00:15:32,848
Who are you?

332
00:15:34,683 --> 00:15:36,602
I think he's banging Gwen's mom.

333
00:15:38,187 --> 00:15:39,188
Yes.

334
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:41,774
Yes, I am.

335
00:15:43,817 --> 00:15:47,279
Oh, and we had just rekindled
the flame to our relationship.

336
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:49,740
Then Fenton just stomped it out.

337
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:51,909
Oh, cry with me.

338
00:15:55,996 --> 00:15:58,874
[sobbing]

339
00:16:00,042 --> 00:16:02,002
Sorry. I can't get water from a stone.

340
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,298
Oh, you two are no help.

341
00:16:07,841 --> 00:16:09,009
I miss my people.

342
00:16:09,093 --> 00:16:10,469
[electric guitar riff plays]

343
00:16:10,552 --> 00:16:13,180
Maybe this life doesn't even matter,
you know?

344
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:15,808
Maybe we're not even here.

345
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:20,437
Or, no. Maybe I'm here, but you're not.

346
00:16:22,564 --> 00:16:24,191
[terrified gasp] Hello?

347
00:16:24,817 --> 00:16:27,111
[laughing]

348
00:16:31,073 --> 00:16:31,991
Oh!

349
00:16:32,783 --> 00:16:33,784
Man.

350
00:16:34,493 --> 00:16:37,162
I just totally forgot why I was laughing.

351
00:16:38,831 --> 00:16:40,708
Isn't that funny? [coughs]

352
00:16:42,084 --> 00:16:44,253
I'm losing my patience with you, man.

353
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:46,547
You gotta get with her.

354
00:16:46,630 --> 00:16:48,674
I mean, there's nothing more beautiful

355
00:16:48,757 --> 00:16:51,844
than when two people
fit together perfectly like…

356
00:16:51,927 --> 00:16:53,470
Well, like two of these potato…

357
00:16:53,971 --> 00:16:55,389
How do they do this?!

358
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:57,933
That's it?

359
00:16:58,434 --> 00:17:02,938
I have to let go of my grudge with Fenton
to fix my relationship with Sherri.

360
00:17:04,189 --> 00:17:06,608
Fez, what are you doing here?

361
00:17:07,484 --> 00:17:10,654
Donna? Oh, this is so great.
The old gang is here.

362
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:15,117
Maybe we should get you some fresh air.

363
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,827
Donna, Donna. I can't.

364
00:17:17,411 --> 00:17:18,912
Eric is my best friend.

365
00:17:18,996 --> 00:17:21,915
[rock music playing]

366
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:31,383
-How?
-I don't know.

367
00:17:32,926 --> 00:17:34,678
-Why?
-I do not know.

368
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:39,683
[groans] He's Jay's best friend.
He's Nikki's boyfriend.

369
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:40,601
He's your brother.

370
00:17:40,684 --> 00:17:41,685
Ugh!

371
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:45,105
This is so bad.

372
00:17:45,773 --> 00:17:46,774
[chuckles]

373
00:17:48,150 --> 00:17:50,611
-Why are you laughing?
-Sorry.

374
00:17:50,694 --> 00:17:53,113
I was just thinking about
the first time we came up here.

375
00:17:53,197 --> 00:17:55,824
You'd never had a beer.
You'd never kissed anyone.

376
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:58,327
You never stopped
talking about debate club.

377
00:17:58,410 --> 00:17:59,286
Oh…

378
00:18:00,037 --> 00:18:01,163
I was such a dork.

379
00:18:01,663 --> 00:18:05,125
But now look at you.
You're an agent of chaos. I love it.

380
00:18:06,710 --> 00:18:08,504
Gwen, what do I do now?

381
00:18:08,587 --> 00:18:10,380
There's nothing <i>to </i>do.

382
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:13,592
You didn't kiss Nate.
You don't owe Jay anything.

383
00:18:14,259 --> 00:18:16,887
So, for now, you go back to Chicago,

384
00:18:16,970 --> 00:18:19,139
you call me every freaking day,

385
00:18:19,223 --> 00:18:20,974
we see each other as much as we can,

386
00:18:21,058 --> 00:18:24,186
and then come back next summer,
and we do it all again.

387
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:26,814
I like this plan.

388
00:18:27,439 --> 00:18:29,483
Hang on. I got you something.

389
00:18:34,154 --> 00:18:35,989
Wanna break one more law before you go?

390
00:18:36,073 --> 00:18:38,617
At this point, why the hell not?

391
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:39,952
[both laughing]

392
00:18:40,035 --> 00:18:43,413
I don't know what you said to Fenton,
but he's completely backed off.

393
00:18:43,497 --> 00:18:46,875
He's getting rid of that tree,
and he promised to re-carpet the bathroom.

394
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:47,918
[Fez chuckles]

395
00:18:48,001 --> 00:18:50,087
Well, I like you,

396
00:18:50,170 --> 00:18:53,090
so I put my ego aside
and, uh, made him a peace offering.

397
00:18:53,757 --> 00:18:56,677
Well, I made that birch my bitch.

398
00:18:58,095 --> 00:18:59,888
Guess I can take this off now.

399
00:19:07,437 --> 00:19:09,481
Take a picture. It'll last longer.

400
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:13,235
[Fez imitates shutter clicking]

401
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:15,904
-[laughs]
-[door shuts]

402
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:17,030
[Fez sighs contentedly]

403
00:19:17,114 --> 00:19:19,825
I got that hair
from a dog groomer. [chuckles]

404
00:19:19,908 --> 00:19:21,034
I win.

405
00:19:21,118 --> 00:19:23,328
Hey, thanks for helping me out
with this, Fez.

406
00:19:23,412 --> 00:19:25,539
Most guys would have just
left me in the lurch.

407
00:19:25,622 --> 00:19:27,708
Oh, hearing you say that
makes me emotional.

408
00:19:28,208 --> 00:19:30,294
And those emotions
are going into my pants.

409
00:19:30,961 --> 00:19:32,504
Oh, my body's such a puzzle.

410
00:19:33,255 --> 00:19:36,341
Well, let's go into the bedroom
and put our pieces together.

411
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:39,219
Oh, I was hoping to have sex, but…

412
00:19:39,303 --> 00:19:41,054
Sure, whatever.
Let's do what you wanna do.

413
00:19:41,138 --> 00:19:45,184
[rock music playing]

414
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:48,103
-Thanks for everything, Grandpa.
-Come here, kiddo.

415
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:51,315
Loved having you around.

416
00:19:51,398 --> 00:19:52,316
You.

417
00:19:53,066 --> 00:19:54,484
But you tell your friends,

418
00:19:54,568 --> 00:19:57,487
the basement is off-limits
while you're gone.

419
00:19:57,571 --> 00:19:59,031
My turn! My turn!

420
00:19:59,114 --> 00:20:00,449
Oh!

421
00:20:00,532 --> 00:20:02,159
I love you, honey.

422
00:20:02,242 --> 00:20:04,745
[cooing] Tell your friends
they can use the basement

423
00:20:04,828 --> 00:20:06,496
as much as they want while you're gone.

424
00:20:06,580 --> 00:20:08,916
Thanks, Grandma. I love you too.

425
00:20:08,999 --> 00:20:10,792
-[laughs happily]
-[Leia] Okay!

426
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:12,419
Grandpa, it's getting tighter!

427
00:20:13,420 --> 00:20:14,338
Kitty!

428
00:20:14,421 --> 00:20:15,505
She's tappin' out.

429
00:20:16,298 --> 00:20:17,382
Hey.

430
00:20:19,092 --> 00:20:21,762
We don't have to talk about it.
It was nothing.

431
00:20:21,845 --> 00:20:22,846
Right.

432
00:20:23,639 --> 00:20:24,473
Really?

433
00:20:25,432 --> 00:20:28,727
-No, it was something.
-Yeah, it was definitely something.

434
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:30,646
Leia!

435
00:20:31,230 --> 00:20:33,273
I'm so glad I caught you before you left.

436
00:20:33,774 --> 00:20:35,442
-Oh. Hey, bro.
-Nothing.

437
00:20:37,736 --> 00:20:38,695
What are you doing here?

438
00:20:38,779 --> 00:20:41,323
I did some soul-searching
and a crap ton of karate,

439
00:20:41,406 --> 00:20:43,408
and I realized I was wrong.

440
00:20:44,284 --> 00:20:45,702
I'm not ready to give up on us.

441
00:20:46,286 --> 00:20:48,664
And… I know I was a jerk,

442
00:20:48,747 --> 00:20:51,333
but if you give me another chance, Leia,

443
00:20:51,416 --> 00:20:54,086
I will spend every day
making it up to you.

444
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:57,256
Jay, that's…

445
00:20:57,756 --> 00:20:59,174
That's so sweet, I…

446
00:21:01,426 --> 00:21:03,762
I'm just a little confused right now.

447
00:21:05,264 --> 00:21:06,515
Maybe this will help.

448
00:21:11,019 --> 00:21:12,229
That was a good one.

449
00:21:13,814 --> 00:21:14,815
Um, Gwen?

450
00:21:15,983 --> 00:21:17,651
She'll call you when she gets to Chicago.

451
00:21:17,734 --> 00:21:19,820
-Not if I call you first.
-Okay, keep it moving.

452
00:21:20,696 --> 00:21:23,490
Okay, Le-Le. Last goodbyes, we gotta go.

453
00:21:23,573 --> 00:21:26,618
-You're calling me soon as you get home.
-Oh, we have a lot to talk about.

454
00:21:27,494 --> 00:21:28,578
Smile!

455
00:21:29,162 --> 00:21:29,997
[shutter clicks]

456
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:32,374
That was the last picture. My job is done.

457
00:21:35,377 --> 00:21:36,420
I am so sorry.

458
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:37,838
-What?
-Nothing.

459
00:21:38,338 --> 00:21:40,841
Get in the car. Get in the car.
Get in the car. Get in the car.

460
00:21:42,759 --> 00:21:44,094
I'm really gonna miss her.

461
00:21:44,177 --> 00:21:45,721
-[car engine starts]
-[Nate sighs]

462
00:21:45,804 --> 00:21:46,722
Me too.

463
00:21:48,473 --> 00:21:50,142
[snickers] Not.

464
00:21:52,394 --> 00:21:57,274
Leia, nooo!

465
00:21:57,357 --> 00:21:58,525
It's okay, buddy.

466
00:21:58,608 --> 00:22:00,902
-[sobbing]
-["Kids in America" by The Muffs playing]

467
00:22:00,986 --> 00:22:04,990
Come back, Leia! Come baaack!

468
00:22:05,073 --> 00:22:07,993
<i>♪ Looking out a dirty old window ♪</i>

469
00:22:08,076 --> 00:22:12,122
<i>♪ Outside the cars in the city</i>
<i>Go rushing by ♪</i>

470
00:22:13,206 --> 00:22:18,045
<i>♪ I sit here alone and I wonder why ♪</i>

471
00:22:19,838 --> 00:22:22,716
<i>♪ Friday night and everyone's moving ♪</i>

472
00:22:22,799 --> 00:22:26,720
<i>♪ I can feel the heat</i>
<i>But it's soothing, heading down ♪</i>

473
00:22:27,971 --> 00:22:31,558
<i>♪ I search for the beat</i>
<i>In this dirty town ♪</i>

474
00:22:31,641 --> 00:22:34,394
<i>♪ Downtown the young ones are going ♪</i>

475
00:22:34,478 --> 00:22:37,230
<i>♪ Downtown the young ones are growing ♪</i>

476
00:22:37,314 --> 00:22:40,150
<i>-♪ We're the kids in America ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Whoa-oh ♪</i>

477
00:22:40,233 --> 00:22:43,028
<i>-♪ We're the kids in America ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Whoa-oh ♪</i>

478
00:22:43,111 --> 00:22:46,573
<i>♪ Everybody live for the music-go-round ♪</i>

479
00:22:48,950 --> 00:22:51,828
<i>♪ Bright lights, the music gets faster ♪</i>

480
00:22:51,912 --> 00:22:56,291
<i>♪ Look, boy, don't check on your watch</i>
<i>Not another glance ♪</i>

481
00:22:57,000 --> 00:23:01,797
<i>♪ I'm not leaving now, honey</i>
<i>Not a chance ♪</i>

482
00:23:03,507 --> 00:23:06,259
<i>♪ Hotshot, give me no problems ♪</i>

483
00:23:06,343 --> 00:23:10,931
<i>♪ Much later, baby</i>
<i>You'll be saying never mind ♪</i>

484
00:23:11,515 --> 00:23:14,976
<i>♪ You know life is cruel</i>
<i>Life is never kind ♪</i>

485
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:17,771
<i>♪ Kind hearts don't make a new story ♪</i>

486
00:23:17,854 --> 00:23:20,649
<i>♪ Kind hearts don't grab any glory ♪</i>

487
00:23:20,732 --> 00:23:23,568
<i>-♪ We're the kids in America ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Whoa-oh ♪</i>

488
00:23:23,652 --> 00:23:26,321
<i>-♪ We're the kids in America ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Whoa-oh ♪</i>

489
00:23:26,405 --> 00:23:30,325
<i>♪ Everybody live for the music-go-round ♪</i>

